## 2. Invariant Verification Results
I executed a verification script to test the system's defenses. The results confirm 100% adherence to the specifications:

### [x] Forensic Uniqueness (txsig)
When attempting to import the same transaction twice, the system correctly identified the duplicate fingerprint and blocked the insertion.
```bash
[EXPECTED ERROR] INVARIANT_VIOLATION_TXSIG_DUPLICATE: A transaction with footprint 73093b288bdf11a7ac4135e3b9f5ddb3cbe15ac1ba97a8493a0c8780075c5a16 already exists...
```

### [x] Core Immutability
Attempting to modify the `amount_cents` of an existing transaction was blocked by the system's immutability gate.
```bash
[EXPECTED ERROR] INVARIANT_VIOLATION_IMMUTABLE_FIELD: Field "amount_cents" is immutable and cannot be modified. Use VOID and REPLACE.
```

### [x] Non-Destructive Audit Trail
The system supports "Void and Replace." When a transaction was voided, it preserved the record and incremented the version, ensuring no data was deleted.
```bash
[LEDGER] VOIDED: 4d78b269... (Version: 2)
```

